{
  "stem": "20035.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "By the way, where we lived, that suburb of Budapest was 20 miles west of Budapest, where from Austria and Czechoslovakia, the German army came in, heading towards Budapest.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And so we had the-- let's call it the occupation or the invasion prior to the city of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Well, naturally the radio station and the other political center of the city or the center of Hungary was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then I don't know if I mentioned to you before right now, actually, I have-- I have three children.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that afternoon my parents sat down with us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And although there was a little bit of rejection from my mom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But the conclusion was that next morning, Monday morning, everybody has to go occupation or no occupation, to go to work.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "That's mean, go to the place where you belong.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And that morning, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] with a little bit of tears in her's eyes, mom packed our lunch.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We took our school bag Monday morning.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we went to school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We had to take-- well, usually it was that we took a train.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was an express train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We had the first-- only one stop going into the Budapest.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "From there, we took the streetcar.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Now, I mentioned to you that I have three children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And the reason I'm mentioning it now, that I hope that never in my lifetime or their life-- or their lifetime, they ever have to come to a conclusion of that's importance or that magnitude, what my parents had to do at that time.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "But if, God forbid, that would happen, I would have told them, or I would came-- I will try to convince them of the same thing, that regardless what happens, you have to go to where you belong, which was school.",
      "word_count": 41
    }
  ],
